{"SlimeBasic":{"!ObjectScript":"res://assets/Scripts/Actors/BaseActor.gd","!ParentKey":"#BaseActor","#ObjDetails":{"Description":"@@#Color:Red:Slimes@@ are gelatinous blobs of biological paradoxes with no discernible sensory organs, digestive system, or really anything resembling \"anotomy\". It was once believed their lack of eyes should render them @@#EftDef:AilmentBlind:Link@@. But instead, the @@#Color:Blue:PAGE@@ System errors in registering a @@#Color:Red:Front@@ or @@#Color:Red:Back@@ and defaults to perfect @@#Stat:Awareness@@. Similarly, their malleable forms have no measurable amount of @@#Stat:Armor@@, yet still demonstrate high @@#Tag:Resistant@@ to all forms of @@#Tag:Physical@@ damage. Despite these abnormalities, researchers have been able to prove that @@#Color:Red:Slimes@@ will die if stabbed enough and thus, meet the scientific definition of \"Life\". But the council still does not grant them the @@#Color:Blue:Tag@@ of @@#Tag:Living@@.","DisplayName":"Slime","LargeIcon":"Sprites/BlueSlime_Icon.png","ObjectType":"Actor","SmallIcon":"Sprites/BlueSlime_Icon.png","SnippetDesc":"A slime.","Tags":["Slime"],"Taxonomy":["Actor"]},"ActorData":{"DropItemsSet":{"":5.0,"HealthPotionM":1.0,"HealthPotionS":5.0,"SlimeSpike_ActionPage":1.0,"Slime_PageBook":1.0},"ExpValue":80.0,"Faction":"Slimes","IsAdirectional":true,"MoneyValue":15.0},"AiData":{"ActionsArr":["MoveForward","MoveBack","MoveLeft","MoveRight","SlimeSpike_ActionPage"]},"CorpseSprite":null,"DefaultPageSlotSet":[{"Count":6.0,"DisplayName":"Any Page","FilterData":null,"Key":"Any"}],"DropItemsSet":{"":1.0},"EquipmentSlots":[],"ImmuneToEffects":["AilmentBlind"],"ScenePath":"Scenes/slime_actor_node.tscn","SpawnEquipmentArr":["Slime_PageBook"],"SpawnItemArr":[],"SpawnPageArr":["SlimeBase_TitlePage","MoveForward","MoveBack","MoveLeft","MoveRight","SlimeSpike_ActionPage"],"SpriteFrameWH":[12.0,4.0],"SpriteOffset":[0.0,0.0],"SpriteSheet":"Sprites/BlueSlime_SpriteSheet.png","Stats":{"Agility":10.0,"Armor":0.0,"Awareness":5.0,"Evasion":20.0,"HealthMax":12.0,"Intelligence":5.0,"MagAttack":0.0,"Mass":2.0,"MinStat:Awareness":5.0,"PPR":4.0,"PhyAttack":10.0,"Resistance:Blunt":80.0,"Resistance:Crash":80.0,"Resistance:Light":0.0,"Resistance:Pierce":80.0,"Resistance:Poison":100.0,"Resistance:Slash":80.0,"Speed":25.0,"Strength":10.0,"Ward":0.0,"Wisdom":5.0},"_DefVersion":"1"},"SlimePoison":{"!ParentKey":"SlimeBasic","#ObjDetails":{"Description":"With a high tolerance to toxins and poor personal hygiene, @@#Color:Red:Slimes@@ often become polluted with whatever is in their environment. After a @@#Color:Red:Slime@@ ingests enough material with @@#Tag:Magical@@ properties, the @@#Color:Blue:PAGE@@ System appears to misinterpret the @@#Color:Red:Slime@@ as possessing the same properties of the given material. At this point, the @@#Color:Red:Slime@@ will alter it's color to conform to cultural norms.\n\n@@#Color:Red:Green Slimes@@ have absorbed large amounts of poisonous plants, toxic waste, and internet comment sections. Any contact with these them is recognized as @@#Color:DmgColor:Poison:Poison Damage@@ and can be potent enough to inflict deadly @@#EftDef:AilmentPoisoned:Link@@ status to the idiot who touched it with their bare hands.","DisplayName":"Green Slime","LargeIcon":"Sprites/GreenSlime_Icon.png","ObjectType":"Actor","SmallIcon":"Sprites/GreenSlime_Icon.png","SnippetDesc":"A slime.","Tags":["Slime"],"Taxonomy":["Actor"]},"ActorData":{"DropItemsSet":{"":5.0,"HurtPotionM":5.0,"HurtPotionS":5.0,"SlimePoisonSkin_PassivePage":1.0,"Slime_PageBook":1.0},"ExpValue":80.0,"Faction":"Slimes","IsAdirectional":true,"MoneyValue":15.0},"ImmuneToEffects":["AilmentBlind","AilmentPoisoned"],"SpawnPageArr":["SlimePoison_TitlePage","SlimePoisonSkin_PassivePage","MoveForward","MoveBack","MoveLeft","MoveRight","SlimeSpike_ActionPage"],"SpriteSheet":"Sprites/GreenSlime_SpriteSheet.png","Stats":{"Resistance:Poison":200.0}}}